Extensions: Finite sums

Key theorem:
\begin{theorem}[Summing over disjoint events] First version
\begin{displaymath}
P(E) = \sum P(E_i)
\end{displaymath}
If $E = \cup E_i$ and $E_i \cap E_j = \emptyset$.

Second version
\begin{displaymath}
P(E) = \sum P(E \cap A_i)
\end{displaymath}
If $\Omega = \cup A_i$ and $A_i \cap A_j = \emptyset$.
\end{theorem}

